                                         JOHANNESBURG - Northern Cape police have discovered and raided dagga plantations worth more than R150,000. The farmsteads were discovered at two separate yards at Ncweng Village.  The police’s Olebogeng Tawana says two suspects aged 30 and 55 were arrested and are facing charges of dealing in drugs. “A dagga plantation was discovered on two separates yards over the weekend at Ncweng Village near Kuruman. Two suspects were arrested and are facing charges of dealing in dagga.”